column5: That only enforces how ethical Skywagon adventures are... they believe even walleye deserve a handicap. Tbayfisher, enjoy your stay in Red Lake, make sure to hit Lac Seul while you are up that way, that is my favorite side of the lake.
McKenzie bay could arguably be the best walleye fishery in Ontario.
Well iam sure he caught fish on that red line.In the fish Spectrom they dont see red well or blue.Which is the color line i use tied direct to jig.Works well.

Yes he did and does catch fish! Red and Blue are my favorite (throw in gold) jig colors. Maybe red and blue are "camo" colors to walleye making the jig invisible to da' fishy's. He's also a good boat partner, but don't tell him that. Pooch
Took a job in red lake -madsen, they are building a new gold mine. Perhaps 4 months. Staying on the Chikuni river, bringing the boat of course. Things aren't so bad. Watch out walleye.
We fished Red Lake July 11-18 out of Sunset Lodge. Lots of spots to choose from. Our best fishing was early AM and the evening fishing.
Is NewGold down south of Nestorfalls doing anything i see NewGold stock is at 1.60 !

All is not lost Eckohlt, it is not too late to book your virtual fishing trip with Skywagon Adventures! For a nominal fee the Skywagon crew will fly to Wapesi lake for a day and film us catching the fish that you have been dreaming of. Catch and release, no fish will be harmed in the making of this film. You will have the pleasure of being there in absentia, watching from the comfort of your home and avoiding those pesky mosquitos at the same time, while helping out the local economy. For more information on this incredible offer contact Skywagon Adventures in beautiful North West Ontario to book a trip of a lifetime.
